article.description: — Dom London had 22 points as Florida Gulf Coast easily defeated Webber International 112-39 on Friday night.
article.headline: Florida Gulf Coast routs Webber International 112-39
article.linkText: Florida Gulf Coast routs Webber International 112-39
article.story: FORT MYERS, Fla. -- — Dom London had 22 points as Florida Gulf Coast easily defeated Webber International 112-39 on Friday night. Cyrus Largie had 14 points for Florida Gulf Coast (4-2). Franco Miller Jr. added 12 points, 10 assists and seven rebounds. Qwanzi Samuels had seven rebounds. Dakota Rivers had a career-high six blocks plus seven points. It was the first time this season Florida Gulf Coast scored at least 100 points. Kris Goettert had seven points for the Warriors. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
